data.name: exportFlagsToStepManiaToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: This will export all the flags for songs to StepMania's preferred sort text format. Note that Preferred Sort doesn't actually support a song in more than one folder without a fork (or modifying the source code).

data.name: label7.ToolTip
data.value: The DDR version this song first appeared in. 19 is a special case, as DDR A won't display it if the series ID is above 18. This can be used to hide the song from the series folders but still have them pickable in the alphabetical, genre, or other game folders.

data.name: label12.ToolTip
data.value: How the song's video will be displayed. A more detailed explanation: 1 - The video will stretch to fit the available screen width. 2 - The video will fit to screen, producing black bars on the left and right if it's a 4:3 video on an HD cabinet. 3 - The video is used as a stage BGA. 4 - The video will be zoomed to fit the screen height, cutting off the sides if it's a 16:9 video on an SD cabinet.

data.name: label27.ToolTip
data.value:
0 (or absent) = unlocked 1 = locked 2 = may be unlocked (it may check <event> in combination) 3 = locked for Premium Play (Challenge-only stepcharts has this tag) 4 = FINAL STAGE song 5 = Extra Exclusive Lv1 6 = Extra Exclusive Lv2 7 = Extra Exclusive Lv3 8 = "ENDYMION" tag <- This tag makes the song accessible on Extra Exclusive Lv3, plus, you're forced to use all the heat gaug prior playing. Clearing makes you access Encore Extra. 9 = ENCORE EXTRA STAGE <- Ace For Aces only has this tag.
Tags 8 and 9 are DDRA only. A20 uses tag 6 up to current official build (2019072400)

data.name: label36.ToolTip
data.value: If anything other than 0, locks a challenge chart. 1 - server lock? 2 - server lock? 3 - eAmusement Pass required 4 - Final Stage 5 - Extra Level 1 6 - Extra Level 2 7 - Extra Level 3 8 - Extra Level + (Endymion)
